00:00:02.009 --> 00:00:04.450
MALE SPEAKER: We are thrilled
to host Sean Gerrity, who

00:00:04.450 --> 00:00:08.220
is the president of the American
Prairie Reserve and a National

00:00:08.220 --> 00:00:09.720
Geographic Explorer.

00:00:09.720 --> 00:00:12.645
And the aim of the
American Prairie Reserve

00:00:12.645 --> 00:00:17.320
is to return to the golden era
of large scale conservation

00:00:17.320 --> 00:00:18.220
in the United States.

00:00:18.220 --> 00:00:21.720
They aim to create
a wildlife preserve

00:00:21.720 --> 00:00:25.450
in the prairies of Montana,
four times bigger than Yosemite,

00:00:25.450 --> 00:00:28.880
in a size that will eventually
rival that of the Serengeti

00:00:28.880 --> 00:00:29.710
in Africa.

00:00:29.710 --> 00:00:33.380
And so in order to accomplish
that, there's the land deals,

00:00:33.380 --> 00:00:36.040
there's the acquisitions,
the plans within the park.

00:00:36.040 --> 00:00:40.200
But as Sean will say in his
speech today, the questions

00:00:40.200 --> 00:00:42.580
and the issues that it
raises are far wider,

00:00:42.580 --> 00:00:46.070
looking at migration patterns
with birds, with animals.

00:00:46.070 --> 00:00:48.620
It's really a program of
nationwide importance.

00:00:48.620 --> 00:00:50.330
And so he will go
through and talk

00:00:50.330 --> 00:00:52.200
about what the
foundation is up to

00:00:52.200 --> 00:00:54.660
and show some of the
latest work and some images

00:00:54.660 --> 00:00:55.787
from the reserve.

00:00:55.787 --> 00:00:57.870
And we'll have time for
some questions at the end.

00:00:57.870 --> 00:01:00.020
So please join me in
welcoming Sean to Google.

00:01:00.020 --> 00:01:00.725
Thank you.

